02/09/2005
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- The city of Istanbul hosted a landmark meeting Thursday (1 September) between Israeli Foreign Minister Silvan Shalom and his Pakistani counterpart, Khurshid Mehmood Kasuri. Both sides described the event as a diplomatic breakthrough, voicing hope that it would mark a new step in Middle East peace process.
Also Thursday, Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan flew to Naples, Italy where he will receive an award for his efforts to strengthen cultural ties. He then travels to the northern town of Como to attend the Ambrosetti Forum, an international summit that brings together heads of state, senior representatives of European institutions and other experts. This year the forum will discuss the latest economic and political developments in the EU. (Turkish Daily News, IRNA, NTV - 01/09/05)
